<item>
            <title>[JDK-8298526] JFR: Generate missing filename for time-bound recordings</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8298526</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>start jfr with duration&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
jcmd 31514 JFR.start duration=30s&lt;br/&gt;
31514:&lt;br/&gt;
Started recording 1.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Use jcmd 31514 JFR.stop name=1 filename=FILEPATH to copy recording data to file.&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
use JFR.check after 30s&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
jcmd 31514 JFR.check&lt;br/&gt;
31514:&lt;br/&gt;
Recording 1: name=1 duration=30s (stopped)&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Unable to close the stopped jfr&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
jcmd 31514 JFR.stop name=1 &lt;br/&gt;
31514:&lt;br/&gt;
Can&amp;#39;t stop an already stopped recording.&lt;br/&gt;
```</description>
